*dbase_numrecords*

(PHP 5 < 5.3.0, dbase 5, dbase 7)

dbase_numrecords â€” Gets the number of records in a database

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  dbase_numrecords ( resource $dbase_identifier ) : int~

Gets the number of records (rows) in the specified database.

  Note:

  Record numbers are between 1 and dbase_numrecords($db), while field numbers
  are between 0 and dbase_numfields($db)-1.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{dbase_identifier}

  The database link identifier, returned by |dbase_open| or |dbase_create|.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The number of records in the database, or FALSE if an error occurs.

===============================================================================
[ Changelog ]

  Version                         Description
dbase 7.0.0 {dbase_identifier} is now a resource instead of an int.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 Looping over all the records of the database

<?php >

  // open in read-only mode
  $db = dbase_open('/tmp/test.dbf', 0);

  if ($db) {
    $record_numbers = dbase_numrecords($db);
    for ($i = 1; $i <= $record_numbers; $i++) {
        // do something here, for each record
    }
  }

<?>

